# Recipe App - Server side

YumCards is a small React/Node/Mongo app to share small/quick recipes.

This is a projec from the React21K gorup of the Business College Helsinki

## Technologies used

Built with: 

- React
- Node.js
- Mongo.db

## Setup and usage

- This project is made together with the Client side of the app, available at https://github.com/aortizpalma/recipeapp_client_side

- npm install body-parser cors express mongoose nodemon
- Adjust package.json's script section as follows:
"scripts": {
  "start": "nodemon index.js"
  },
- Run "npm start" on the server root directory to run the backend on the port 5000
- To connect to the Mongo.db cluster you may require Netowk Acess from me for your specific IP address.

## Screenshot

## Sources 

Package dependencies:
- body-parser: enables to send post requests
- cors: enables cross-origin requests
- express: for the routing framework of the app
- mongoose: to create models for the posts
- nodemon: allows to prevent having to reload the server every time a change is made

